               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of ʻAqāʼid-i Nuṣratīyah by Ḥabīb ibn Miyān Kashmīrī</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://id.loc.gov/authorities/subjects/sh85130552 http://id.loc.gov/authorities/subjects/sh85068396" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1550-item1">
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>On Sunni theology and the essentials of orthodox belief and practice by Ḥabīb ibn Miyān ʻAbd al-Raḥīm ibn Muḥammad Mīnā of Kashmir. Written at the request of a prince 
                <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f8016" role="pat">Shams al-Dīn Muḥammad Nuṣrat ibn Malik Muḥammad</persName>.
                        </p>
                        <p>The work consists apparently of 2 sections (rukn) and a khatimah, but this copy lacks the end of the first section and the conclusion.</p>
                        <p>ff. 263; 17 lines to a page; Persian naskhi with additions in another hand; rubrications; dated 7 Sha’ban 1079 (10 Jan 1669).</p>
                     </note>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f8035">Ḥabīb ibn Miyān Kashmīrī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa" key="person_f8035">حبیب ابن میان کشمیری</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_23035">ʻAqāʼid-i Nuṣratīyah</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_23035">عقائد نصرتية</title>
                  </msItem>
